article.headline: Yale 57, Columbia 49
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Ross Morin and Alex Zampier both scored 16 points to lead Yale over Columbia 57-49 on Saturday night. Patrick Foley led all scorers with 17 points for Columbia but Yale went on a lengthy run in the second half and rallied from a nine-point deficit to pull away in the game's final minutes. Jason Miller added 10 points for the Lions. Both teams are now 11-13 on the season and tied for second place in league play at 6-4. Columbia led 27-25 at the half and then built a 41-32 lead with 14:03 to play in the second half. But Yale went on a 16-2 run as the Lions scored just one field goal over a 10-minute span. Morin had 12 of his points in the second half and Yale did the bulk of its scoring in the paint or on the free throw line.
